      "content": "that makes sense. so the \"instability\" is basically just the physical pulsing of the wave interference. besides the beating, is there anything about the way our brain interprets that specific \"clash\" that makes it feel more \"harsh\" or \"jarring\" than other intervals? like is it just the speed of the beating, or is there more to it?",
