      "content": "Yes, besides the physical pulsing of the beating, the brain's interpretation also plays a role. Research suggests that the brain emphasizes the differences in frequency and the consequent beating effect when they are within a relatively narrow interval, making near-intervallic relationships like minor seconds sound dissonant. This phenomenon is often referred to as the \"near-intervallic accentuation.\" Furthermore, the brain's tendency to filter out or downstage harmonic or near-harmonic frequencies contributes to the perceived dissonance.",
